tions.\nRaw collections have uninteresting views.\nCollections are very similar and have a lot of boilerplate code.\nMany views are just collections, as are the results of searches, and some queries encoded as actions.\n  </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <h2>\nSolution\n  </h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <p>\nWrap collections of domain objects in a dedicated group wrapper, and give it dedicated views, actions and searches.\n  </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <h2>\nSteps\n  </h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <p>\nUse the TGroupWithItems trait. Call the collection “items”.\nShow examples from the ESUG website.\nWherever you need to show a collection of these objects, just forward the view to the wrapper to avoid duplicated the view code.\nIf you have gtSearches, be sure they return the collection wrapper.\n  </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <h2>\nRelated patterns\n  </h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"snippet textual-snippet text-snippet paragraphWidth\">\n  <p>\n<a href=\"viewable-data-wrapper-9jkob08ts9ihwg72kvyccl5ff.html\">Viewable data wrapper</a>.\n  </p>\n</div>\n      <div class=\"footer\">\n        <p>Want to go back to the <a href=\"/\">list of posts</a>?</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"
